A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Sheriff Gary Gulledge; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Sheriff Gary Gulledge served with honor and distinction as the 47th sheriff of
3 the Paulding County Sheriff's Office from 2008 until his retirement in 2024, concluding his
4 exemplary 34-year career in law enforcement where it first began in 1990; and
5 WHEREAS, throughout his career, Sheriff Gulledge held roles such as jailer, patrol deputy,
6 warrant officer, and K-9 deputy, with much of his pre-sheriff service spent in the K-9
7 Division, where he and K-9 Basco became the first dual purpose K-9 team in the
8 department's history; and
9 WHEREAS, as sheriff, he remained accessible to his constituents, represented the Office of
10 Sheriff with fairness and professionalism, and played a critical role in overseeing the
11 department's growth, including the development of a new training facility in 2016 and the
12 design and construction of a new law enforcement facility and detention center in 2020; and
13 WHEREAS, he contributed to law enforcement initiatives across the state, serving on the
14 Georgia Sheriffs' Association Board of Directors and Legislative Committee as well as its
15 regional vice president for Region 1; and
