16 WHEREAS, he further served as part of the Georgia Commission on Medical Cannabis, the
17 Georgia Department of Corrections Board, the Advisory Board of the Northwest Georgia
18 Law Enforcement Training Center, and as chairman of the Haralson-Paulding Drug
19 Taskforce Control Board; and
20 WHEREAS, Sheriff Gulledge's unyielding commitment to public safety has left a lasting
21 impact on Paulding County and set a high standard for future generations of law enforcement
22 professionals; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
24 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body commend the care, courage, sympathy, and selfless dedication
27 exhibited by Sheriff Gary Gulledge in carrying out the difficult duties of his vocation,
28 congratulate him upon the grand occasion of his retirement, and extend the most sincere best
29 wishes for continued health and happiness.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Sheriff Gary Gulledge.
